SIMPLE: unformed
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unformed
<hw>Un*formed"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[In sense 1
properly p. p. of <ets>un form</ets>; in senses 2 and 3 pref.
<ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>formed</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Decomposed, or resolved into parts; having the form
destroyed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not formed; not arranged into regular shape, order,
or relations; shapeless; amorphous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Unorganized; without definite
shape or structure; <as>as, an <ex>unformed</ex>, or unorganized,
ferment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Unformed stars</b></col> <fld>(Astron.)</fld>, <cd>stars
not grouped into any constellation; informed stars. See
<er>Sporades</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unfortunate</ent>⟦br⟧
